    <stitle>CAB: 2000, 4000, AND 8000 - REMOVE AND INSTALL - OUTER DOOR HANDLE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="2">
        <title>OUTER DOOR HANDLE</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>The outer door handle (Item 5,
                <hotlnk document="s16007s_30.xml" xrefid="f1600739">Figure 39</hotlnk>) is a combination handle and
                lever operating assembly that connects with the door latch assembly (Item 4,
                <hotlnk document="s16007s_30.xml" xrefid="f1600738">Figure 38</hotlnk>) inside door to actuate the latch
                jaws (Item 2,
                <hotlnk document="s16007s_30.xml" xrefid="f1600737">Figure 37</hotlnk>). The outer handle can be removed
                and installed without removing latch assembly.
            </para>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Remove</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove door hardware and trim, if so equipped. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16007s_20.xml" xrefid="x1600706">Hardware and Trim, Remove</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove hex nuts (Item 3,
                    <hotlnk document="s16007s_30.xml" xrefid="f1600739">Figure 39</hotlnk>) from studs on inside of
                    door.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1600741">Figure 41</hotlnk>for Items in parentheses.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1600741" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1600741" filename="../figg16/G1600741.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 41. Lock Cylinder Assembly</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. ROD END CLIP/LOCK CYLINDER ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. LOCK CONTROL ROD</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. DOOR LATCH CONTROL ROD</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. OUTER DOOR HANDLE</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the door latch control rod (Item 3) from the outer handle (Item 4), then unfasten
                    rod end clip at lock cylinder assembly (Item 1) and remove lock control rod (Item 2).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove outer door handle (Item 1,
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1600742">Figure 42</hotlnk>) from door.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1600742" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1600742" filename="../figg16/G1600742.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 42. Outer Door Handle</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. OUTER DOOR HANDLE</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Install</title>
            <para>The outer door handle (Item 5,
                <hotlnk document="s16007s_30.xml" xrefid="f1600739">Figure 39</hotlnk>) is a combination handle that
                connects with the door latch assembly (Item 4,
                <hotlnk document="s16007s_30.xml" xrefid="f1600738">Figure 38</hotlnk>) inside the door to actuate the
                latch jaws (Item 2,
                <hotlnk document="s16007s_30.xml" xrefid="f1600737">Figure 37</hotlnk>). Outer handle can be installed
                without removing the latch assembly.
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position outer door handle (Item 1,
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1600742">Figure 42</hotlnk>) on door. Secure with hex nuts (Item 3,
                    <hotlnk document="s16007s_30.xml" xrefid="f1600739">Figure 39</hotlnk>) on studs on inside of door.
                    Tighten until snug.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Attach the door latch control rod (Item 3,
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1600741">Figure 41</hotlnk>), then attach lock control rod (Item 2,
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1600741">Figure 41</hotlnk>) to lock cylinder assembly (Item 7,
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1600741">Figure 39</hotlnk>) and secure with rod end clip (Item 1,
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1600741">Figure 41</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install door hardware and trim, if so equipped. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16007s_20.xml" xrefid="x1600707">Hardware and Trim, Install</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
